Anh - Anh
jade
jade1
■ noun
1》 a hard, typically green, stone consisting of the minerals jadeite or nephrite, used for ornaments and jewellery.
2》 the light bluish green colour of jade.
Origin
C16: from Fr. le jade (earlier l'ejade), from Sp. piedra de ijada 'stone of the flank' (i.e. stone for colic, which it was believed to cure).
————————
jade2
■ noun archaic
1》 a bad-tempered or disreputable woman.
2》 an old or worn-out horse.
Origin
ME: of unknown origin.

sentences.en: This white jade pendant is a real buy.

sentences.en: It's said the real jade will resist any scratching with metal.
sentences.vi: Người ta nói rằng ngọc bích thật thì không bị trầy xước khi cọ xát với kim loại.
